Prevention of accidental ammonia releases at The Wine Group?s Franzia Winery Sanger Facility is accomplished through sound industry practice in the original design and construction of the ammonia refrigeration system (i.e. double-block scenario relief valves, ASME cylinders), the specification and review of system modifications, and the day-to-day operation and maintenance of the systems.
This includes:
? Compliance with industry standards and codes in effect at the time of initial construction and modification;
? Performance of Process Hazard Analyses (PHAs) at least once every five years; 
? Implementation of Operating Procedures which have been reviewed by PHA; 
? Appropriate initial and refresher training of system operations and maintenance personnel;  
? Performance of preventive and corrective maintenance ;
? Application of established auditing, inspection, and pre-start-up review protocols; and
? Use of qualified contractors for work on the system.
